Red Hat Documentation Access Training:

When accessing content from docs.redhat.com that uses dynamic JavaScript loading (resulting in only CSS/JavaScript without actual content),
use these URL transformation patterns:

STANDARD URL FORMAT:
https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/{product}/{version}/html/{guide}/index

ALTERNATIVE FORMATS:

1. PDF FORMAT (MOST RELIABLE):
- Replace "/html/" with "/pdf/"
- Add ".pdf" extension with naming pattern: {Product_Name}-{version}-{Guide_Name}-en-US.pdf
- Example:
  Original: https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/red_hat_openshift_logging/6.4/html/release_notes/index
  PDF: https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/red_hat_openshift_logging/6.4/pdf/release_notes/Red_Hat_OpenShift_Logging-6.4-Release_notes-
en-US.pdf

2. HTML SINGLE FORMAT (SECONDARY OPTION):
- Replace "/html/" with "/html-single/"
- Keep rest of path unchanged
- Example:
  Original: https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/red_hat_openshift_logging/6.4/html/release_notes/index
  HTML Single: https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/red_hat_openshift_logging/6.4/html-single/release_notes/index

USAGE PRIORITY:
1. Try PDF format first (usually best for content extraction)
2. Use HTML single as fallback
3. These patterns are consistent across all Red Hat documentation

Apply these methods automatically when encountering docs.redhat.com URLs that return only page structure without content.
